topics.title: Conclusion
topics.coverage_text:
I've had, like, I've personally played around with PID tuning on this build
and had D gains at 50 or 55+, without really seeming to have much sign of smoked motors,
but everybody's build is going to be different.
But before we start doing our test flights,

And I'm not really sure why Betaflight does this.
Betaflight, by default, limits the PID controller to 40% of its maximum authority.
And if it exceeds that, then, well, it's not allowed to exceed that.
